"Vasili I. Galchin" <vigalchin@gmail.com> asks:

>       What and when was the motivation of the lifting concept?

When? "Way back when." What? -- lifting paths in a base space
to paths in a covering of it. See, for example the "lifting"
and "homotopy lifting" entries in Sze-Tsen Hu's classic 20th C. =

textbook {Homotopy}, in Academic Press, circa 1960. =


Of course that work isn't the origin of the lifting concept.
But it does discuss the motivation quite plainly and carefully. =


This may start you on an interesting and fruitful journey
to earlier works, perhaps as far back as to Weyl's {Riemann
Surfaces} or beyond.

-- FEJ Linton



